menu "breadboard: bb_sink_mqtt"

config BB_SINK_MQTT_QOS
    int "Default MQTT QoS level for telemetry publishes"
    default 0
    range 0 1
    help
        MQTT Quality-of-Service level used by bb_sink_mqtt when publishing
        telemetry payloads. 0 = at-most-once (fire-and-forget, lowest
        overhead); 1 = at-least-once (acknowledged delivery, required by
        AWS IoT Core for reliable ingestion). Default 0 matches the prior
        hardcoded value (no behavior change). Set to 1 for AWS IoT Core
        deployments. QoS 2 is not supported by bb_sink_mqtt.

config BB_SINK_MQTT_RETAIN
    bool "Set the MQTT retain flag on telemetry publishes"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, telemetry messages published via bb_sink_mqtt carry
        the MQTT retain flag so the broker stores the last message per topic
        and delivers it immediately to new subscribers. Default n (retain
        off) matches the prior hardcoded value (no behavior change). Enable
        for deployments where dashboard tools rely on retained state (e.g.
        Home Assistant auto-discovery).

endmenu
